RIYADH: The Secretary General of the Gulf Cooperation Council Nayef Falah Al-Hajraf met with Bahrain’s Foreign Minister Abdullatif bin Rashid Al-Zayani in Manama on Sunday. The meeting came as the GCC chief approaches the end of his tenure at the council. Al-Zayani praised Al-Hajraf’s great efforts to support joint GCC action, its unity and solidarity, and his service to its causes. The foreign minister also hailed the endeavours of the secretary general to cement the progress of the council in order to meet the aspirations and ambitions of member states. Al-Hajraf expressed his sincere gratitude and appreciation for Bahrain’s support for the council’s work.